104
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:44,980
Don't worry.

105
00:15:47,140 --> 00:15:48,540
I'll ask Erjing to take you back.

106
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:51,820
After you go back, just focus on recovering from your injury.

107
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,300
You will get better.

108
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:57,260
I'm sure of that.

109
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:03,660
Uncle Erbai.

110
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:06,300
Trust me.

111
00:16:10,780 --> 00:16:12,660
Have faith in me, just this once.

112
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:26,580
Goodbye, Uncle Erbai.

113
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:33,540
Mr. Third Junior.

114
00:18:34,740 --> 00:18:35,460
Have some porridge.

115
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:38,540
Thank you.

116
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,100
I'm fine.

117
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:56,140
I'm fine.

118
00:18:57,580 --> 00:18:58,260
Mr. Third Junior.

119
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:02,340
There's something Your uncle Erbai wouldn't let me tell you.

120
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,540
But now I am desperate.

121
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:07,260
Before he and I came here,

122
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:09,420
we found another access.

123
00:19:10,060 --> 00:19:11,700
But it's too dangerous.

124
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,940
That's why we chose to

125
00:19:13,940 --> 00:19:15,460
focus on the entrance to Thunder City at Spring of Roar.

126
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:17,940
Where is that access?

127
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:26,340
Look.

128
00:19:28,620 --> 00:19:30,060
This is Tianlin Building we're at now.

129
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,140
Isn't there a mountain next to it?

130
00:19:32,740 --> 00:19:35,340
You'll enter a forest area from behind the mountain.

131
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:37,380
Walk for three days in it,

132
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:39,700
and you'll see a cliff.

133
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,620
Below this cliff

134
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:45,620
is the exit of Spring of Roar.

135
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:47,380
When you go down from here,

136
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:50,940
you might be able to find Thunder City from another direction.

137
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:56,300
Goodbye.

138
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:11,740
How can I get off the cliff?

139
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:12,620
With a parachute.

140
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:14,220
But

141
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:15,700
none of the people we sent there to try

142
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:17,460
came back alive.

143
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:20,100
Mr. Erbai felt that this way was too risky,

144
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:21,060
so later on,

145
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:22,820
we gave up this option.

146
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:24,820
Mr. Third Junior.

147
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,620
Mr. Erbai still has some unused parachute bags.

148
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,940
It's up to you whether to go or not.

149
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:30,340
Take me to get the bags.

150
00:21:07,980 --> 00:21:09,420
You don't want to

151
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:11,060
bring me to the party?

152
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,260
But for the adventure this time…

153
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:39,460
it is nearly impossible to return alive, right?

154
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:40,380
I can't remember

155
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:42,140
how many times you have said this.

156
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:44,060
You said so every time.

157
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:45,780
You didn't get bored of it?

158
00:21:46,940 --> 00:21:47,860
Besides,

159
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:49,740
what's the point if an adventure is not dangerous?

160
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,660
I thought you know very well that

161
00:21:53,220 --> 00:21:54,700
the reason why we could have a narrow escape in every adventure

162
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:56,140
was that I was there.

163
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:57,780
We won't be so lucky every time.

164
00:22:00,460 --> 00:22:01,580
I should be dead by now.

165
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:02,820
If I go down there

166
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:04,340
and can find Kylin and Glasses,

167
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:05,460
then it's like a good bargain for us.

168
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:07,540
But you guys are not me.

169
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:09,180
You still have a lot of time ahead of you.

170
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,540
You have a long life to enjoy.

171
00:22:10,660 --> 00:22:12,020
There's no need to go on a suicide mission with me.

172
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:13,540
What are you talking about?

173
00:22:14,340 --> 00:22:16,060
So you are Kylin's only friend?

174
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:17,420
For the past ten years,

175
00:22:17,580 --> 00:22:19,060
it was just the two of you who have been fighting side by side?

176
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:20,220
I'm so jealous!

177
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,620
Was I ever absent for even a minute?

178
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,700
We are called The Trio.

179
00:22:25,860 --> 00:22:27,100
If only two angles go down underground,

180
00:22:27,620 --> 00:22:29,020
leaving one angle on the ground,

181
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,260
you are not afraid that you two can't stand still?

182
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:33,500
I'm jealous too.

183
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:35,500
The four of us have become sworn brothers and sister.

184
00:22:36,540 --> 00:22:38,180
Although I am not willing to admit it,

185
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:39,700
I am like the fourth member of your Trio.

186
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:41,940
I am obliged to find our big brother.

187
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:45,300
You finally admit it.

188
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,100
I know you're a smart girl.

189
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,100
I will go with you too.

190
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,780
Since I decided to come with you guys at the beginning,

191
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:52,140
I won't leave until we finish the task

192
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:54,540
even if it's dangerous.

193
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:56,100
Me, too!

194
00:22:57,060 --> 00:22:58,260
Are you guys still going?

195
00:22:58,620 --> 00:22:59,740
Stop dawdling!

196
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:01,140
I need to go find Chief.

197
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:03,900
Look at how cocky he is.

198
00:23:06,540 --> 00:23:07,380
Erjing said that

199
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:09,620
Uncle Erbai organized a unit to go down there several times.

200
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,340
But none of the people who went down came back.

201
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:13,860
I guess the thick fog is highly poisonous.

202
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,820
And finding the landing point is very important.

203
00:23:17,140 --> 00:23:17,980
With such a heavy fog,

204
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:19,700
once you hit the cliff

205
00:23:19,860 --> 00:23:20,980
and retract the parachute, you will fall to the ground and die immediately.

206
00:23:21,180 --> 00:23:23,420
Here it comes again. You're so pessimistic.

207
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,420
Close your eyes and jump.

208
00:23:25,540 --> 00:23:26,380
That's it!

209
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:30,980
I tested it just now.

210
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:32,900
It is southeast wind with grade 3 to 4.

211
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:34,860
The gorge on the east side has a bigger rift valley.

212
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:37,420
Let's land there.

213
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:40,180
That gorge is so deep that it seems bottomless.

214
00:23:40,380 --> 00:23:42,300
And the wind changes unpredictably now.

215
00:23:42,940 --> 00:23:44,100
If we carry a parachute

216
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:45,180
and just jump like this,

217
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,140
we are very likely to deviate from the original preset point.

218
00:23:47,380 --> 00:23:48,660
And everyone will get separated easily.

219
00:23:49,660 --> 00:23:51,100
So now there is only one way to do it.

220
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:53,020
After we jump,

221
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:54,620
the later you shoot out the parachute, the better.

222
00:23:55,340 --> 00:23:56,940
Shoot it out when we get close to the ground.

223
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:59,180
So that we'll get closer to the preset landing spot.

224
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:01,660
But if we do that,

225
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:03,540
the risk will be greater, too.

226
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:05,180
Say no more.

227
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:08,100
No matter what you choose to do, we will be by your side.

228
00:24:10,900 --> 00:24:12,460
Bai always gives good speech!

229
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:14,180
A bunch of fools.

230
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:17,020
Wish this bunch of fools are blessed.

231
00:26:43,260 --> 00:26:44,100
Are you guys alright?

232
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:53,580
These gas masks don't work!

233
00:26:55,580 --> 00:26:56,300
What should we do?

234
00:26:56,500 --> 00:26:57,940
The poisonous fog is fierce.

235
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:00,260
We need to transfer

236
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,860
to a safer place now!

237
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:02,420
Got it.

238
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:03,060
Let's go.

239
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:05,180
Are you okay?

240
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:06,860
Bai.

241
00:27:07,180 --> 00:27:07,780
Bai.

242
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:08,300
Go.

243
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:30,260
Naive.

244
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:33,980
You finally woke up.

245
00:28:35,620 --> 00:28:36,980
Look who this handsome guy is.

246
00:28:44,420 --> 00:28:45,500
So in the end,

247
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:49,580
it was still you who came to save my ass.

248
00:28:49,980 --> 00:28:50,820
Of course.

249
00:28:50,940 --> 00:28:52,580
Kylin will definitely come for us.

250
00:28:54,860 --> 00:28:56,780
I forgot to hug you.

251
00:28:56,980 --> 00:28:59,340
I miss you so much, Kylin.

252
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:00,860
We'll never separate again.

253
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:01,820
I'm hugging you now.

254
00:29:02,980 --> 00:29:03,660
That's enough. Fatty.

255
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:04,900
Kylin.

256
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:06,020
Let me introduce her to you.

257
00:29:06,140 --> 00:29:07,860
This is the girl I never mentioned to you.

258
00:29:07,980 --> 00:29:09,500
The fourth member of our squad now, Bai.

259
00:29:09,580 --> 00:29:09,980
Bai.

260
00:29:10,060 --> 00:29:12,220
This is our big brother whom I always mentioned to you.

261
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:13,100
Kylin.

262
00:29:13,940 --> 00:29:14,740
Thank you, Kylin.

263
00:29:14,940 --> 00:29:18,020
The four of us finally got together!

264
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:21,460
Kylin.

265
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:23,460
